The paper discusses the affects of software developers in the workplace, which is a topic that falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the influence of affects on cognitive activities, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper provides recommendations for measuring affects, which could be useful in the context of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper touches on the well-being and happiness of software developers, which could be relevant to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
